From: OrangeFox Recovery Patcher <patch@orangefox.recovery>
Date: Mon, 2 Jun 2026 08:51:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Disable keystore2 auto-start to prevent blocking

When crypto is enabled, keystore2 auto-starts and tries to register
with servicemanager, but this can cause blocking issues. Keystore2
should only be started when explicitly needed for decryption.

diff --git a/etc/init/keystore2.rc b/etc/init/keystore2.rc
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/etc/init/keystore2.rc
+++ b/etc/init/keystore2.rc
@@ -6,8 +6,9 @@
 #
 # See system/core/init/README.md for information on the init.rc language.
 
-on late-init
-    start keystore2
+# Disabled auto-start to prevent blocking with servicemanager
+# on late-init
+#     start keystore2
 
 service keystore2 /system/bin/keystore2 /tmp/misc/keystore
     class early_hal
